title.rendered: Bangladesh vs Ireland, 3rd ODI: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Fantasy Team for Bangladesh vs Ireland, 3rd ODI

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Mustafizur Rahman was rested for the previous ODI, while there is no update on Mehidy Hasan Miraz’s injury.

Bangladesh: Tamim Iqbal (c), Litton Das, Najmul Hossain Shanto, Shakib Al Hasan, Towhid Hridoy, Mushfiqur Rahim (wk), Yasir Ali, Taskin Ahmed, Ebadot Hossain, Nasum Ahmed, Hasan Mahmud/Mustafizur Rahman

Ireland: Stephen Doheny, Paul Stirling, Andrew Balbirnie (c), Harry Tector, Lorcan Tucker (wk), Curtis Campher, George Dockrell, Andy McBrine, Mark Adair, Matthew Humphreys, Graham Hume

Pitch Report

Venue: Sylhet International Cricket Stadium, Sylhet

(Based on last three completed games)

1st innings average score: 327

2nd innings average score: 230

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 100%

Batting 2nd: —

Also Read:

Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 1st T20I 2023: Fantasy Tips

South Africa vs West Indies, 1st T20I: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Tamim Iqbal provides plenty of fantasy points when he bats in Sylhet. In six innings, he has accumulated 417 runs at a staggering average of 104, including two hundreds.

Najmul Hossain Shanto is having a good time in white-ball cricket. He has collected 457 runs, including five half-centuries, in the last 10 outings.

Harry Tector and Paul Stirling have done the bulk of the scoring for Ireland since 2021. Together, they have smashed seven centuries and average 50.

Shakib Al Hasan generates points one way or the other against Ireland. Besides averaging 36 with the bat, he has bagged 13 wickets.

Mushfiqur Rahim has scores of 100*, 44, and 70 in his last three ODIs, also giving bonus points for strike rate twice. In addition, he generated handy points for six catches.

Graham Hume has scalped 11 wickets in the last five ODIs.

Mark Adair and Ebadot Hossain have featured in the Best11 in each of the last five matches.

After four ODIs, Andrew Balbirnie averages only 12 versus Bangladesh.

All three centuries registered in the last three completed games at the venue belonged to openers.
